  "body": "Hi, I think I've found an issue starting geth using \"geth console\" and --targetgaslimit\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: Geth/v1.8.12-stable-37685930/windows-amd64/go1.10.3\r\nOS & Version: Windows\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nThe geth node votes to increase the block gas limit when the targetgaslimit is set higher than the current limit using --targetgaslimit\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nThe geth node votes to decrease the block gas limit\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n1. Have a private blockchain with a starting gaslimit higher than the default.\r\n2. Start geth using \"geth console ..... --targetgaslimit <higher than it currently is>\"\r\n3. Repeatedly check the gas limit using eth.getBlock('latest').gasLimit\r\n4. See the gas limit decrease.\r\n",
